## Status: COMPLETED ✅

## Summary

Wired the existing `RateLimiter` (from `security.rs`) into the
`call_tool_handler` dispatch boundary (M3.3) and wrapped the per-tool
match block with a `tokio::time::timeout` whose duration is selected
from the tool's `cognicode_meta.category` (M3.2). Both new failure
modes are surfaced as `InterfaceError::Internal("timeout")` and
`InterfaceError::Internal("rate_limit_exceeded")` and recorded in the
M1.6 error metric as separate `error_type` values.

## Tasks Completed

### M3.2 — Per-tool timeout

- [x] Added `timeout_for_category(category: &str) -> Duration` in
  `rmcp_adapter.rs`. Returns `60s` for `graph`, `45s` for
  `navigation`, `500ms` for `search`, `30s` for `file`/`aix`/
  `composite`/`quality`/`refactor` and the unknown fallback.
- [x] Added `tool_category_map()` — a lazily-initialised
  `HashMap<String, String>` keyed by `Tool::name`, values are
  `cognicode_meta.category`. Built once from `build_all_tools()` on
  first access; falls back to `"unknown"` for tools absent from the
  map.
- [x] Wrapped the per-tool `match` block in `call_tool_handler` with
  `tokio::time::timeout(timeout, dispatch).await`. On `Elapsed`, the
  dispatch future is dropped and we return
  `InterfaceError::Internal("timeout".to_string())`.

### M3.3 — Rate limit enforcement

- [x] Added `with_strict_rate_limit(max_tokens, window_secs)` builder
  on `InputValidator` — swaps in a stricter `RateLimiter` for
  callers that want a global override.
- [x] Added `pub fn rate_limiter(&self) -> &RateLimiter` accessor
  on `InputValidator`.
- [x] Added `pub fn rate_limiter(&self) -> &RateLimiter` accessor
  on `HandlerContext` (delegates to the validator's limiter so the
  HTTP and dispatch paths share the same per-key state).
- [x] Defined `STRICT_RATE_LIMIT_CATEGORIES = ["graph", "navigation",
  "aix"]` — the categories that get a `strict:<tool_name>` rate-limit
  key prefix (separate namespace from the regular `tool:<tool_name>`
  budget) so heavy tools cannot exhaust the rest of the dispatcher.
- [x] In `call_tool_handler`, computed `rate_key` per tool and called
  `ctx.rate_limiter().check_with_key(&rate_key)` BEFORE the match
  block. On rate-limit hit, the boundary emits the M3.4 structured
  log line, records the OTel `calls` + `duration` + `errors` metrics
  (with `error_type="rate_limit_exceeded"`), and returns
  `InterfaceError::Internal("rate_limit_exceeded")`.
- [x] Updated the M1.1 `error_type` match in `call_tool_handler` to
  recognise the new sentinels:
  ```rust
  InterfaceError::ToolNotFound(_) => "missing",
  InterfaceError::Internal(msg) if msg == "timeout" => "timeout",
  InterfaceError::Internal(msg) if msg == "rate_limit_exceeded" => "rate_limit_exceeded",
  _ => "error",
  ```

